# Flutter / Dart Patterns — ProFinancas Frontend

## Folder Structure

```
lib/
  main.dart
  models/        # Data classes matching DRF serializers
  services/      # API calls (HTTP layer)
  screens/       # Full-page widgets (one file per screen)
  widgets/       # Reusable UI components
  providers/     # State management
```

## Models

- Mirror the DRF serializer fields exactly (names, types)
- Always implement `fromJson` / `toJson`
- Use `const` constructors where all fields are final

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
class Transaction {
  final String id;
  final String type; // 'INCOME' | 'EXPENSE'
  final double amount;
  final String description;
  final DateTime transactionDate;

  const Transaction({required this.id, required this.type, required this.amount, ...});

  factory Transaction.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => Transaction(
    id: json['id'],
    type: json['type'],
    amount: (json['amount'] as num).toDouble(),
    transactionDate: DateTime.parse(json['transaction_date']),
  );
}
```

## Widgets

- Prefer `const` constructors for stateless widgets
- Extract reusable pieces into `widgets/` — do not repeat UI logic in screens
- Name screens with `Screen` suffix, reusable widgets without it

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
class TransactionCard extends StatelessWidget {
  const TransactionCard({super.key, required this.transaction});
  ...
}
```

## API Service Layer

- All HTTP calls live in `services/` — never call `http` or `dio` directly from screens
- Base URL should reference the Django backend (`http://10.0.2.2:8000/api/` for Android emulator)
- Always handle errors and return typed results

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
class TransactionService {
  Future<List<Transaction>> getTransactions() async {
    final response = await _dio.get('/transactions/');
    return (response.data as List).map((e) => Transaction.fromJson(e)).toList();
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — HTTP call inside a widget
onPressed: () async {
  final res = await http.get(Uri.parse('http://...'));
}
```

## Conventions

- Use `snake_case` for files and directories, `PascalCase` for class names
- Always pass `super.key` in widget constructors
- Financial amounts are `double`; display using `NumberFormat.currency` from `intl`
- Transaction type constants: `'INCOME'` and `'EXPENSE'` (uppercase strings, matching backend)
